Ho ho ho Hoi An! Christmas this year was spent in the joyus town that is Hoi An (Incase you didn't get the joke!)

Our very nice and WARM christmas was spent lounging by the riverside (in our santa hats), cruising down the river (in our santa hats) and taking part in a gourmet cooking course at the Red Bridge cooking school in their outdoor kitchen terrace.... (in our santa hats!)

Rather than bore you with the details, here are lots of photos of us on our Vietnamese Christmas Day :D

